            <h4 class=3D"mb-3">What is Wordificator?</h4>
            <p class=3D"text-muted">
              Wordificator creates images made entirely of words, arranged =
inside any
              selected shape. Upload your own silhouette or choose from a l=
arge library of ready-made shapes.
              Adjust fonts, colors, sizes, orientations and let the algorit=
hm do the work and place the words.
            </p>
            <p class=3D"text-muted">
              Enter a list of words, pick a font and a color palette, and p=
ress <strong>Generate word art</strong>.
              The process can take a few seconds, especially on slower devi=
ces like smartphones, so please be patient. Finally, you can export a high-=
resolution PNG for
              editing and printing or share your creation directly on Pinte=
rest.
            </p>


<h4 class=3D"mb-3">Create pictures made from words</h4>

<p>With Wordificator you can create:
  </p><ul>
	<li>Word art with any shape or silhouette</li>
	<li>Text pictures made from your own words</li>
	<li>Typography art for posters and prints</li>
	<li>Word clouds with custom layouts</li>
	<li>Text-into-shape designs such as hearts, animals or logos</li>
  </ul>
<p></p>
<p>All generated directly online, ready to download.</p>


            <h4 class=3D"mb-3">Work in progress</h4>
            <p class=3D"text-muted">
              Wordificator is constantly evolving and new features, fonts, =
and color palettes are added regularly. If you have suggestions, requests, =
or ideas for improvement, feel free to reach out.
              You can contact me anytime at <a href=3D"mailto:contact@wordi=
ficator.com">contact@wordificator.com</a> - I=E2=80=99d love to hear from y=
ou.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class=3D"col-12 col-md-6">
            <h4 class=3D"mb-3">How it works</h4>
            <p class=3D"text-muted">
              Wordificator uses a custom layout engine designed to place wo=
rds inside any shape with pixel-level precision. The process begins at the =
center of
              the shape and moves outward along a randomized spiral path, t=
esting thousands of possible positions for each word. At every point, the a=
lgorithm c
              hecks whether the word fits inside the silhouette and whether=
 it overlaps any previously placed words.
            </p>
            <p class=3D"text-muted">
              Larger words are placed first, followed by smaller ones to fi=
ll in remaining gaps. Color, orientation, and font settings influence how e=
ach
              word is rendered. This combination of deterministic structure=
 (spiral expansion) and randomness (orientation, spacing jitter, word order=
)
              produces layouts that are both visually balanced and organica=
lly irregular, resulting in clean, high-quality word art every time.
            </p>
